<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a193601-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6707"><num value="6707">§ 6707.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a193602-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6707/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is authorized to be appropriated to carry out this chapter $15,000,000 for each fiscal year.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a193603-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6707/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Limitation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No funds made available under subsection (a) shall be used to pay the costs of constructing any facilities.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a193604-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/317/s8">Pub. L. 108–317, § 8</ref>, <date date="2004-10-05">Oct. 5, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/1210">118 Stat. 1210</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
